products2.name: Bee Bread
products2.description: Bee bread is a small pellet containing pollen, along with nectar or honey. The exact bee bread composition varies depending on the plants the bees have foraged from. Often confused with bee pollen, bee bread is a fermented version, which is regarded as having a higher nutritional value. It is the bee’s saliva, containing a vast range of probiotic bacteria and yeast, which kicks off the fermentation process and increases the bioavailability of the super food.

products2.name: Bee Propolis
products2.description: Bees produce a compound called propolis from the sap on needle-leaved trees or evergreens. It is used as a sealant for unwanted open spaces in the hive.

products2.description: Pollen honey, also known as Pollen Infused honey, is considered to be a healthier alternative to Natural honey. Pollen honey contains antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals that are beneficial for overall health.

products2.description: Bee Pollen Capsules are dietary supplements made from bee pollen, a powdery substance collected by bees from the stamen of plants. Bee pollen is a rich source of nutrients, including vitamins, minerals, amino acids, and antioxidants.

products2.description: Propolis honey is a type of honey that is made by bees using the resin from trees and plants. Propolis honey has been shown to have strong antibacterial properties, making it useful for treating a variety of infections and wounds.
